olive oil
½ Onion
1 white turnip
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
1 packet Halloumi
1 sachet Kiwi Spice Blend
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 packet Crispy Shallots

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut onion (see ingredients) into quarters. Cut white turnip into bite-sized chunks.
• Place onion, turnip and peeled pumpkin pieces on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• When the veggies have 5 minutes cook time remaining, cut hamoumi into 1cm slices.
• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook halloumi and Kiwi spice blend until golden brown, 1-2 minutes each side. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.

• To the tray of roast veggies, add baby leaves and toss to combine.

TIP: Transfer veggies and baby leaves to a bowl if your tray is getting crowded.

• Divide roast pumpkin toss between plates. Top with smokey halloumi.
• Dollop over dill & parsley mayonnaise. Sprinkle with crispy shallots to serve. Enjoy!